    <h1> Exercise 1 </h1>
    <p> Notes on HTML.</p>
    <ol>
        <li>always use "<>" when starting a new code </li>
        <li>always start code with "html","head","title", and "body"</li>
        <li>different elements:</li>
                <ol type="a">
                    <li> type "p" to start a paragraph or any writing</li>
                    <li> type "h1" to make a heading (can use other numbers 1-10 to make smaller)</li>
                    <li> use "br" to start a new line</li>
                    <li> use "hr" to add a line between paragraphs</li>
                </ol>
        <li> Lists: </li>
                <ol type="a">
                    <li>start with "ol" for ordered list (1,2,3)</li>
                    <li>start with "ul" for unordered list or bullet points</li>
                    <li> use "li" for each line of the list</li>
                </ol>    
        <li> Tables:</li>
                <ol type="a">
                    <li>type "table" to start </li>
                    <li>type "tr" to start a new row</li>
                    <li> inside "tr" use "th" for heading and "td" for normal text</li>
                    <li> if borders are wanted, use "table, th, tr, td{
                        border: 1px solid black;
                        border-collapse: collapse} in style in the begining of code.</li>
                </ol>
        <li> Images:</li>
                <ol type="a">
                    <li>to add an image, must download image to a folder</li>
                    <li>type "img src= image/" and type file name</li>
                    <li> if image needs to shrink, type "width=" and number of px wanted</li>
                </ol>
        <li> Links: </li>
                <ol type="a">
                    <li> to add a link to seperate page type "a href=" and name of other page</li>
                </ol>
    </ol>
